hopobject.body: Your account's overdrawn discount famvirial Getting deeper the differences between the two devices become starker. The Nexus 7 features a screen with an impressive 1,920-by-1,200-pixel resolution. Kindle Fire HD features a screen of considerably lower resolutions at 1,280-by-800. The Kindle Fire HD features only a front facing camera of 1.3 MP and there is no rear camera. The Nexus 7 features a 5 MP rear camera and a secondary front camera of 1.2 MP.
